    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-04T03:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-04T03:34:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1977: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-04T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 5—10:21 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Manchuria Station frontier opened with some restrictions by the Chinese
                    authorities today. This should improve Chinese Eastern earnings so they can get
                    through March but will not enable them to make any headway against overdue
                    liabilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
